A drink-driver has been shamed on Twitter by police after he crashed his car next to a neon sign - warning about the dangers of drink-driving.

The unnamed man left his car parked at a 90 degree angle and wedged next to the lamppost which had a matrix sign reading 'Don't drink and drive'. 

The motorist was breath tested at the scene in Cheltenham, Gloucester, where he gave a reading of 75mg of alcohol in 100ml of breath - almost twice the legal limit. 

He was immediately arrested on suspicion of drink driving on Sunday evening.

