An officer, in his 40s, who has served with the force for 11 years was knocked unconscious and sustained a broken leg.

His colleague, a PC also in his 40s and who has served with West Midlands Police for 13 years, suffered serious fractures to both legs.

The officers were given emergency first aid by colleagues at the scene in Tipton, before specially trained firearms officers arrived to give assistance.

They were rushed to hospital where they remained yesterday evening. The driver of the Golf, who is from the Dudley Port area of Tipton, was trapped in the car and needed to be cut free by firefighters.

She was taken to hospital with a suspected broken shoulder where she was arrested on suspicion of drink driving and will be questioned when she is released by medics.

 

 

